{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS 1 review — T11 (Data-migration / backfill safety) [overlay]: PASS, no findings.\n\nAffirmations:\n- T11 (online / expand-contract): The \"Migration\" is a lazy, per-ticket reducer SEED computed at reduce/restore time from current deps + parent_id (\"On the FIRST reduce/restore where `managed_refs` is absent ... the reducer SEEDS it from the ticket's CURRENT deps + parent_id\"). This is a derived field reconstructed from the event log on every read — not a blocking DDL on a large table — so the no-downtime / expand-contract concern is satisfied by construction. Confirmed against src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py:515 (process_snapshot restores compiled_state field-by-field on every reduce).\n- T11 (batching/scale): Per-ticket, recomputed on read; no giant single transaction to batch. The plan also notes per-ticket ref cardinality is small (tens). Not-applicable by construction.\n- T11 (resumability/idempotency): Seeding is inherently idempotent and resumable — deterministically recomputed on every reduce; a partially-completed run simply re-derives on the next read. No double-apply window.\n- T11 (dual-write window): No cutover window exists — the new field/event is \"preserved-and-ignored by older clones (forward-compatible rollout; fsck WARNs on newer-than-binary state).\" Writes during rollout are not lost because state is re-derived each reduce.\n- T11 (rollback / data-loss): Explicit back-out posture documented — \"disabling the fold leaves the gate a safe no-op\" and \"Missing/absent managed_refs defaults to EMPTY => the gate returns False (degrade to additive-only: no remove, no clobber, no churn-delete).\" Partial failure degrades to additive-only with no data loss.\n\nRationale for PASS: T11 is an overlay for persisted-format DDL / large-table backfills requiring online/batched/cutover execution. This change is a non-persisted, lazily-derived reducer field (ANTI-FP: not-applicable for in-memory changes), and the plan's own text affirmatively covers the residual rollout/back-out concerns. No T11 findings."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782537376193808001,"uuid":"f5e8e716-85ab-4810-8cd8-95cd549503cc"}